(33, 5, 'Does Bluetooth Printer Work with iPhone Device?', '<p>Yes, it does. The iPhone provides several options to print wirelessly from the device. Apart from AirPrint, you can use Bluetooth technology to print documents directly from your device. The iPhone has a Bluetooth transmitter that enables users to send documents to printers. Bluetooth connections help the device connect with the printer and print rigorously without interruptions.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-08-10 04:02:22', '2023-08-10 04:02:22'),
(34, 5, 'Why is My iPhone Failing to Connect to My Bluetooth Printer?', '<p>The iPhone can fail to connect to the printer and print essential documents. Have you tried pairing the device with your printer, but it failed? Here is something you will need to check then.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>First, confirm that the Bluetooth signal is on.&nbsp;<br></li><li>Move to your printer and turn on its Bluetooth.</li><li>Ensure your printer and iPhone are within the Bluetooth range of connection.&nbsp;</li><li>Check if there are errors on your iPhone.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2023-08-10 04:02:22', '2023-08-10 04:02:22'),
(35, 5, 'How Can I Connect Bluetooth Printer to My iPhone?', '<p>You can connect your Bluetooth printer to your iPhone using a few steps below. Execute them cautiously to print without any errors.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Go to Settings on your iOS device.&nbsp;</li><li>Click on Settings and go to Bluetooth.&nbsp;</li><li>Toggle the Bluetooth option ON on your device.&nbsp;</li><li>Next, create a Printer Station.&nbsp;</li><li>Type in a name for your printer and click on the no printer select option.&nbsp;</li><li>Finally, select Connect a Bluetooth Printer and execute all the on-screen prompts.</li></ol>', '2023-08-10 04:02:22', '2023-08-10 04:02:22'),
(36, 6, 'What are the Manual Steps to Connect a Printer to Mac Via Bluetooth?', '<p>Printer users can easily connect their device to Mac with the help of a Bluetooth connection. Here are a few instructions they can follow.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>First, add the device manually.&nbsp;</li><li>Next, go to the <b>Device</b> tab</li><li>Now, choose the option -&nbsp; <b>Add a Device.</b>&nbsp;</li><li>Run that installation wizard.&nbsp;</li><li>Once you see your printer in the list, use the<b> Add Printer</b> option wizard.&nbsp;</li><li>Now, select the <b>Bluetooth</b> printer from that wizard.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2023-08-10 04:49:01', '2023-08-10 04:49:01'),
(37, 6, 'How to Connect Printer to Mac OS X 10.9 or Later?', '<p>Follow these easy steps to connect your printer to Mac OS X 10.9 - or Later.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Open the <b>Apple menu</b>, followed by <b>System Preferences</b>.&nbsp;</li><li>Click on <b>Bluetooth</b>.&nbsp;</li><li>If Bluetooth is off, turn it <b>ON</b>.&nbsp;</li><li>Next, move to your printer and press and hold the<b> Bluetooth</b> button.&nbsp;</li><li>Select your printer’s name on the <b>Mac</b> screen.&nbsp;</li><li>Finally, click on the <b>Pair</b> button to connect.</li></ul><p>In case you need help connecting, reach out to printer experts. Visit the <b>Support</b> page of bluetoothprintersetup.com and ask for a <b>free consultation</b>.&nbsp;<br></p>', '2023-08-10 04:49:01', '2023-08-10 04:49:01'),
(38, 6, 'Why is my laptop not Pairing with a Bluetooth Printer?', '<p>The laptop may fail to connect to a Bluetooth printer. Here are the reasons.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>You have not turned on the Bluetooth of our laptop.</li><li>The bluetooth light of your printer is not pulsing.&nbsp;</li><li>Your printer is communicating with another device.&nbsp;</li><li>You have connected the printer to a USB cable.&nbsp;</li><li>Your laptop is displaying some error messages.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2023-08-10 04:49:01', '2023-08-10 04:49:01'),
(39, 7, 'Do Wireless Printers Use Bluetooth?', '<p>The top printer brands bring several printer models that support wireless connectivity. You can find the Bluetooth-enabled printer and use your device to connect with them. To make a connection, make sure to keep the machine in range. Bluetooth connectivity is easy and time-saving to set up. But, the connectivity is ideal for small office spaces with fewer users.<br></p>', '2023-08-10 05:35:58', '2023-08-10 05:35:58'),
(40, 7, 'What are the Best Wireless Bluetooth Printers in 2023?', '<p>Bluetooth printers feature several features. It delivers quality prints, fast print speeds, and other features, such as multi-function. Furthermore, look at some of the best printer models from the top brands.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>HP ENVY 6055e printer</li><li>Canon PIXMA TR4520 Printer</li><li>KODAK Step Printer</li><li>Polaroid Hi-Print Printer</li><li>Xerox Workcentre 3025ni Multi-function Printer</li><li>Epson TM-P20 Direct Thermal Printer</li><li>Samsung ProXpress SL-M3370FD Multi-Function Printer</li><li>Brother QL-820NWB Wireless Wi-Fi Bluetooth Printer</li></ul>', '2023-08-10 05:35:58', '2023-08-10 05:35:58'),
(41, 7, 'Which Printer Can I Consider Better, Bluetooth or a Wi-Fi Printer?', '<p>Bluetooth printers use low-power wireless networks. It connects devices that are within the range. Also, the devices are easy to maintain, just with Bluetooth compatibility. Connecting the printer doesn’t need routers, wires, or a network. However, this connectivity is okay for smaller companies, but a Wi-Fi-connected printer is needed for big organizations.<br></p>', '2023-08-10 05:35:58', '2023-08-10 05:35:58'),
(45, 8, 'What are Common Bluetooth Problems in Printers?', '<p>Here are some of the common issues with Bluetooth printers.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Computer or mobile phone not being able to detect the printer.&nbsp;</li><li>Getting a lot of connection errors between printer and mobile.&nbsp;</li><li>The printer receives offline while printing a document or performing any job.&nbsp;</li><li>Your printer and PC/smartphone should be within the range.&nbsp;</li><li>Correct Bluetooth settings can refrain printers from connecting, and many more.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2023-08-11 05:39:21', '2023-08-11 05:39:21'),
(46, 8, 'How Do I Fix Common Issues in a Bluetooth Printer?', '<p>Use the follow-up methods to fix the common issues in your Bluetooth printer.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Check the Bluetooth on your printer and the other device you are trying to connect it to.&nbsp;</li><li>Make sure the printer driver is up-to-date and genuine.&nbsp;</li><li>Uncheck the \'Use Printer Offline\' option on your computer.&nbsp;</li><li>Restart the printer to get rid of minor glitches.&nbsp;</li><li>Run the factory reset of the printer to get it.&nbsp;</li><li>Set the printer as default to avoid offline issues.&nbsp;</li><li>Remove any third-party components from the printer machine and others.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2023-08-11 05:39:21', '2023-08-11 05:39:21'),
(47, 8, 'Is Taking Professional Help to Fix the Printer a Good Idea?', '<p>Fixing the printer\'s issue depends on your expertise in the printer. Also, some of the minor problems go away quickly just by restarting the printer. On the other hand, some cases require so much effort to fix the problem. Hence, you can seek professional help according to the difficulty level of resolving the issue. Also, taking the experts can fix your device without you breaking a sweat.&nbsp;</p>', '2023-08-11 05:39:21', '2023-08-11 05:39:21'),
(48, 9, 'How Can I Connect My X500-10T Laptop to HP Bluetooth Printer?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Implement these simple\r\nsteps to connect your laptop to an HP printer via Bluetooth. It will easily\r\nconnect the printer.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Initially, connect your HP printer to a power outlet. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Switch on your printer and turn on your printer’s Bluetooth.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">After that, ensure the printer is discoverable.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Then, move to your laptop’s </span><a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Bluetooth     setup</a><span lang=\"EN\"><b>.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Now, tap on the search for nearby devices.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Select your printer when the system displays your printer, <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">In the end,\r\n     install the printer drivers through a CD or HP printer’s official site.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-08-30 05:12:44', '2023-08-30 05:12:44'),
(49, 9, 'Does the HP Printer Work With Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Yes, it does. A\r\n<b><a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/hp/hp-bluetooth-printer-setup-on-windows-and-mac\" target=\"_blank\">Bluetooth printer model</a></b> allows users to print wirelessly. However, to do so,\r\nusers need to connect the system by enabling Bluetooth features. Whether you\r\nhave a <b>Mac</b> or <b>Windows</b> computer, you can easily connect your HP printer by\r\nfollowing appropriate prompts. But, while you connect the printer, keep it\r\nwithin the range.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-08-30 05:12:44', '2023-08-30 05:12:44'),
(50, 9, 'How to Pair Computers With HP Printers With Built-in Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">There are some <b>HP\r\nprinters</b> with built-in Bluetooth. You can use it to pair your computer. Follow\r\nthese effortless steps for the process.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">First, turn on your printer’s <b>Bluetooth</b>\r\n     button.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Now, open the <b>Bluetooth\r\n     settings</b> and enable the feature.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">After that, select your printer from the available devices list.</span></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\">Finally, follow the steps and add your printer.</li></ol>', '2023-08-30 05:12:44', '2023-08-30 05:12:44'),
(54, 10, 'How to Connect the Canon Printer With Laptop via Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Some of the steps you\r\ncan execute for the procedure are as follows:</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">First, head to your laptop. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">After that, open the <b>Control\r\n     Panel.</b><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Now, move to the<b> Printers\r\n     and Devices</b> and then <b>Bluetooth\r\n     Devices. </b><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Next, turn on your Canon printer.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Check on the box - <b>My\r\n     device is set up and ready to be found.</b><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Lastly, tap on the <b>Next</b>\r\n     button and complete the process.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-09-06 03:58:20', '2023-09-06 03:58:20'),
(55, 10, 'How to Connect a Canon Bluetooth Printer in Windows 10?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">You can pair your\r\nprinter easily on a Windows 10 computer. Here are a few steps you are required\r\nto follow.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">First, toggle the Bluetooth on. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Click on the <b>Add Bluetooth</b>\r\n     or other device option.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Select <b>Bluetooth </b>as the\r\n     type of device you need to connect. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Now, start to pair your system and the printer. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Move to <b>Device Manager </b>and\r\n     check the <b>COM port.</b><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">In the end, install the print driver.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-09-06 03:58:20', '2023-09-06 03:58:20'),
(56, 10, 'Can I Connect My Canon Printer to Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Yes, you can. If your\r\nprinter has a Bluetooth feature, you can connect the printer easily for\r\nprinting efficiency. However, for better results, you can use the </span><a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/canon/canon-bluetooth-printer-setup-guide-for-windows-and-mac\" target=\"_blank\"><b>Canon printerinkjet or SELPHY app</b></a><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\"><b></b> from the <b>App Store</b>\r\nor<b> Google Play Store</b> as per your\r\ndevice. Please note that it is not a guarantee that all Android devices support\r\nthe Bluetooth connectivity option.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-09-06 03:58:20', '2023-09-06 03:58:20'),
(60, 11, 'How to Connect Brother Bluetooth Printer to iPhone?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Here are the enlisted\r\nsteps that you can execute to connect the printer. But, before beginning, turn\r\non your printer and ensure the battery is charged.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Go to <b>Settings</b> on your <b>iPhone</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Now, toggle the <b>Bluetooth </b>button\r\n     to enable it.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">After that, you have to expand the options. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Select <b>Printer</b> from the\r\n     <b>iOS settings</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Enter your printer\'s name and click the <b>No Printer Selected </b>option. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Arial;color:#0E101A;mso-ansi-language:EN;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Finally, select the <a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/brother/brother-bluetooth-printer-setup-on-computer-and-mobile-devices\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\"><b>Connect a Bluetooth Printer</b></a> option and follow all the steps.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', '2023-09-12 02:42:31', '2023-09-12 02:42:31'),
(61, 11, 'How Can I Connect My Brother Printer and Computer Using Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">It is a simple and\r\nhassle-free process. But before you proceed, make sure to look into the steps <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">below.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Head to the <b>Menu</b> bar. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">When you see the Bluetooth menu, select - <b>Set up Bluetooth Device. </b><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Later, choose your printer from the list of printers.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Next, use a unique passcode to enter the password. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Arial;color:#0E101A;mso-ansi-language:EN;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">At last, when you are on the conclusion screen,\r\nselect - <b>Quit.&nbsp;</b></span><br></p>', '2023-09-12 02:42:31', '2023-09-12 02:42:31'),
(62, 11, 'How to Enable Bluetooth on Brother QL-820NWB Printer?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Are you experiencing\r\nissues in enabling Bluetooth on the <b>QL-820NWB</b> printer? Here are the steps that\r\ncan assist you in the process.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">Go to your\r\n     printer\'s <b>Menu </b>and press the\r\n     button.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Use the up and down arrows to select <b>On/Off </b>Bluetooth. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">After that, you have to hit on <b>OK</b>. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"\"><font color=\"#0e101a\">Again, use the up and down arrows to select <b>Bluetooth</b>, then automatic reconnection. <o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">Tap on the <b>Back </b>button\r\n     and return to the main screen.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:#0E101A;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><span lang=\"EN\">In the end, you can see a <b>Bluetooth\r\n     </b>icon.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-09-12 02:42:31', '2023-09-12 02:42:31'),
(66, 12, 'Why is My Xerox Printer Not Connecting to Computer via Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">If your Xerox printer\r\nis not connected to the computer via Bluetooth, many reasons can be there.\r\nLet’s see them.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">●<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Your printer and computer may not be\r\ncompatible with each other. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">●<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Some hardware issues with your printer. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">●<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Your printer and PC are not within the\r\nrequired range. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">●<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Your devices aren’t connected to the power\r\nsupply properly.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-09-15 05:09:59', '2023-09-15 05:09:59'),
(67, 12, 'How Can I Connect My Xerox Printer to My Mac?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Look at the following steps to connect or\r\nadd your Xerox printer to a Mac device.</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Go to the <b>Apple\r\n     Menu</b> on your Mac device. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Then, tap on the <b>System Preferences</b> option. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Now, move to the <b>Devices and Printers</b> option and tap on it. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Next, click on the <b>plus sign</b> to see the available printers. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Then, go to the top of the window and choose the <b>Default</b> option. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">After that, select your printer and let it add to\r\n     your device.&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2023-09-15 05:09:59', '2023-09-15 05:09:59'),
(68, 12, 'How to Connect Xerox Printer via Bluetooth on Windows?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Here are the steps to connect the Xerox\r\nBluetooth printer to Windows:</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">First, go to the <b>Start menu</b> and select the <b>Devices\r\n     </b>option. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Then, tap on the <b>Bluetooth </b>option. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Now, ensure that the <b>Bluetooth</b> option is turned on. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">After that, your computer will scan for the\r\n     available printers. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">When you see your printer in the list, click on it. </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Let the connection complete.</span></li></ol><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Arial;color:#0E101A;mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">In case you’ve any queries, contact us through\r\nour <b><a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/support\" target=\"_blank\">Support </a></b>option and get\r\nassistance. Our professionals are <b>available\r\n24/7 </b>to help you solve your problem. You can either <b>chat </b>or <b>call </b>us.&nbsp;</span><br></p>', '2023-09-15 05:09:59', '2023-09-15 05:09:59'),
(69, 13, 'How Do I Setup Samsung Bluetooth Printer to My Computer via Bluetooth?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">It\'s easy to set up your\r\nSamsung printer to your computer via Bluetooth. You just need to follow the\r\ngiven steps.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Download a compatible Samsung printer driver through\r\n     HP\'s Support page. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Then, move to the <b>Printers &amp; Devices</b> option on your computer. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Now, ensure that the Bluetooth is <b>ON </b>and click the <b>Add Device</b> option. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">After that, select your printer\'s name from the\r\n     devices list.</span></li></ol><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Finally, the <b><a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/samsung\" target=\"_blank\">Samsung Bluetooth printer setup</a></b> is\r\ncomplete on your computer.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-09-18 04:21:31', '2023-09-18 04:21:31'),
(70, 13, 'Why is My Samsung Bluetooth Printer Not Connecting to My Computer?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">If your <b>Samsung\r\nBluetooth printer</b> is unable to connect to your computer, there could be many\r\ncauses for it, like the fact that your computer may not have the <b>latest printer\r\ndrivers installed</b>. Otherwise, a hardware issue may be a possible reason. Or\r\nelse your printer and computer are not placed correctly, or both devices aren\'t\r\n<b>compatible </b>with each other. You may also forget to turn on your printer.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-09-18 04:21:31', '2023-09-18 04:21:31'),
(71, 13, 'How to Setup Samsung Bluetooth Printer on a Mac?', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\">You can easily set up your Samsung printer to\r\na Mac by following the given steps:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top:0in\" start=\"1\" type=\"1\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">First, browse the <b>HP Support page</b> on an internet\r\n     browser. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Download and install the latest and correct printer\r\n     driver for your operating system. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Now, go to the <b>Devices\r\n     and Printers</b> option from <b>System\r\n     Preferences. </b></span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">After that, tap on the <b>Add Device</b> option. </span><span lang=\"EN\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Next, choose your Samsung printer and select an\r\n     appropriate option on your screen.</span></li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color:#0E101A\">Then, your <b>Samsung\r\nBluetooth printer</b> will be connected to the Mac.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2023-09-18 04:21:31', '2023-09-18 04:21:31');

