<strong>phone call </strong>or <strong>live chat </strong>with our experts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Connect Xerox Printer via Bluetooth on Windows?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When your Xerox printers have all the latest printer drivers installed, you can move to connect it via Bluetooth on your computer. Here are the steps for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>In the first step, go to the <strong>Start menu </strong>on your PC.</li>\r\n	<li>Then, select the <strong>Settings </strong>icon from the options.</li>\r\n	<li>Now, under the <strong>Settings </strong>window, tap the <strong>Devices</strong> option.</li>\r\n	<li>Then, click on <strong>Bluetooth</strong> and other devices in the next window. You can see these options on the left side of your screen.</li>\r\n	<li>On the right side of the screen, turn ON the <strong>Bluetooth </strong>option (Skip the step if it&rsquo;s already on).</li>\r\n	<li>After that, select the <strong>Add Bluetooth</strong> <strong>or other device </strong>option.</li>\r\n	<li>A new window will appear; tap on the <strong>Bluetooth </strong>option.</li>\r\n	<li>Let the printer connect to your PC.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, your Xerox printer is connected to the PC via Bluetooth. Or, if you have faced any issues while connecting the printer via Bluetooth, then you can visit our <a href=\"https://bluetoothprintersetup.com/help-guides\"><strong>bluetoothprintersetup.com</strong></a> site for a<strong> free consultation. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Connect Xerox Printer via Bluetooth on Mac?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Connecting Xerox printers via Bluetooth on a Mac is simple and will take only a few minutes to get connected. Follow the steps below to continue.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Initially, you need to ensure that your Mac software is updated.</li>\r\n	<li>Then, move to the <strong>Apple Menu</strong> and then click <strong>System Preferences</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>Now, click the <strong>Software Update</strong> option.</li>\r\n	<li>Get the software if anyone